@prefix ekga: <https://example.org/ekga/ns#> .
@prefix spec: <https://example.org/ekga/spec/> .
@prefix prov: <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#> .
@prefix dct:  <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix xsd:  <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

spec:ekga-001 a ekga:Specification ;
    dct:title "Enterprise Knowledge Graph Application (EKGA)" ;
    dct:hasVersion "0.1.0-draft" ;
    ekga:status "draft" ;
    dct:created "2026-04-10"^^xsd:date ;
    ekga:intent """Provide a single, versioned, human- and machine-readable source of truth for an enterprise application that captures, manages, and reasons over heterogeneous organizational data through a graph-native knowledge layer. The spec itself must be translatable to RDF so it can be linked to the running system it describes and consumed by downstream AI agents as authoritative context.""" ;
    ekga:purpose """Stand up an enterprise application that unifies a vector store, an RDBMS, and an RDF triplestore behind a governed ontology, with schema-driven editing, LLM-assisted structured extraction, provenance on every graph mutation, and a chat interface backed by persistent agentic memory.""" .

spec:R1.1 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "RDF triplestore: Apache Jena Fuseki, TDB2 backend, named-graph aware." .
spec:R1.2 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "RDBMS: PostgreSQL (default), virtualized into the KG via Ontop (OBDA, OWL 2 QL profile). PK/FK relationships surfaced as object properties in the virtual graph." .
spec:R1.3 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Vector store: pgvector (preferred, co-located with RDBMS) or Qdrant (fallback). Embeddings linked back to RDF resources via stable IRIs." .
spec:R1.4 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "All three stores addressable through a single internal service layer; no direct client-to-store calls outside the service boundary." .
spec:R2.1 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Core ontology: a minimal OWL 2 ontology describing the application itself (modules, users, sessions, ingest jobs, provenance) and the business domain (initially stub classes; extended per deployment)." .
spec:R2.2 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Inferencing: OWL 2 RL rules via Jena reasoner OR Ontop's own rewriting; SHACL (shacl-compact where practical) for structural and closed-world validation." .
spec:R2.3 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Provenance: PROV-O, emitted on every graph write, attributing the change to a user, agent, or module with a timestamp and source activity IRI." .
spec:R2.4 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Entity resolution: every RDF view must expose a resolution hook (default: SHACL-driven key shapes plus configurable string/embedding similarity). Resolved equivalences recorded as `owl:sameAs` in a dedicated `urn:graph:sameas` named graph and optionally materialized into target named graphs." .
spec:R3.1 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Authentication: SAML 2.0 and OAuth 2.0 / OIDC only. Local password auth is prohibited." .
spec:R3.2 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Must support Azure AD on GCC High tenants end to end (metadata exchange, certificate rotation, group claim mapping)." .
spec:R3.3 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Authorization: RBAC with a seeded `admin` role. Roles stored in the KG under `urn:graph:iam` and enforced at the service layer." .
spec:R3.4 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Multi-user: asynchronous parallel transactions required; no real-time collaborative editing in v1." .
spec:R4.1 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Clean, minimal web UI. Recommended stack: React plus a shadcn/ui-style component library, or HTMX plus server-rendered templates for a lower-dependency path." .
spec:R4.2 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "RDBMS lookup view: table browser with filter, sort, paginated read, and in-cell edit for permitted tables." .
spec:R4.3 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "RDF query view: SPARQL editor (YASGUI or equivalent) with named-graph selector and saved-query support." .
spec:R4.4 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Schema-driven forms: generated from SHACL node shapes, with JSON Schema as an interchange format where a SHACL-to-JSON-Schema transform is available." .
spec:R4.5 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Chat view: conversational panel with streamed responses, citations back to source IRIs, and a memory inspector." .
spec:R5.1 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Register new RDBMS sources through the UI, capturing connection metadata, Ontop mapping file, and responsible owner. Registration writes a record into the KG under `urn:graph:registry`." .
spec:R5.2 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Holonic ingest: consume external holons with awareness of named graphs, membranes, and holon boundaries; preserve source graph identity on import." .
spec:R5.3 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Generic RDF ingest: accept any RDF serialization. Sources with insufficient write metadata are flagged read-only." .
spec:R5.4 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Every ingest produces a PROV-O activity record." .
spec:R6.1 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Pluggable LLM connector layer. Must support at least one local or open-source model backend (vLLM, Ollama, or llama.cpp) in addition to vendor APIs." .
spec:R6.2 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Structured extraction via Pydantic schemas (Instructor or Pydantic-AI patterns), with schemas derived from or validated against the target SHACL shapes." .
spec:R6.3 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Extraction context: the LLM is given a distilled view of the relevant ontology fragment and recent graph neighborhood so outputs align with existing IRIs and vocabulary." .
spec:R6.4 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Extracted triples land in a quarantine named graph, validated against SHACL, and only promoted on review or auto-promotion policy." .
spec:R6.5 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Every extraction writes provenance (model, prompt hash, source document IRI, reviewer)." .
spec:R7.1 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Chat answers draw from SPARQL over the KG, vector retrieval, and, where appropriate, direct RDBMS queries through the virtual graph." .
spec:R7.2 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "User turns and assistant responses are persisted to a Fuseki dataset `urn:graph:memory` with user, session, and turn IRIs. Initial memory strategy: load recent turns for the active session plus top-k semantic recall from prior sessions." .
spec:R7.3 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Memory writes are PROV-O annotated." .
spec:R8.1 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "FOSS preference: prioritize well-vetted open-source components." .
spec:R8.2 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Deployment: containerized (OCI images), Helm chart for Kubernetes, docker-compose for single-node dev." .
spec:R8.3 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Observability: structured logs, OpenTelemetry traces, Prometheus metrics." .
spec:R8.4 a ekga:Requirement ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Backup and restore for all three stores." .
spec:US1 a ekga:UserStory ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "As an admin, I register a new PostgreSQL source, upload an Ontop mapping, and see its tables appear as a virtual named graph." .
spec:US2 a ekga:UserStory ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "As a data steward, I open a SHACL-driven form for a domain class, fill fields, submit, and the resulting triples appear in the target named graph with provenance." .
spec:US3 a ekga:UserStory ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "As an analyst, I run a SPARQL query across the virtual RDBMS graph and a holon-ingested graph, join on resolved `owl:sameAs` links, and export the result set." .
spec:US4 a ekga:UserStory ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "As a knowledge engineer, I configure an extraction pipeline over a directory of PDFs, review the quarantine graph, and promote validated triples." .
spec:US5 a ekga:UserStory ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "As any authorized user, I ask a question in chat, receive a grounded answer with IRI citations, and the interaction is preserved to memory." .
spec:US6 a ekga:UserStory ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "As an admin, I add a user, assign a role, and the change is reflected in the IAM named graph and enforced on next request." .
spec:designnote-40ee392a a ekga:DesignNote ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Treat the spec itself as RDF: each section above maps to an `ekga:Requirement`, `ekga:UserStory`, or `ekga:DesignNote` individual, linked to the application components it constrains." .
spec:designnote-56ef66f2 a ekga:DesignNote ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Prefer SPARQL and SHACL as the primary control surfaces; Python only where graph operations are insufficient." .
spec:designnote-4b4fc5ea a ekga:DesignNote ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Keep the bootstrap ontology small and extend per deployment rather than shipping a heavy domain model." .
spec:designnote-f9a73080 a ekga:DesignNote ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Entity resolution must be observable and reversible; `owl:sameAs` decisions carry provenance and can be retracted." .
spec:designnote-b7261dc7 a ekga:DesignNote ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Chat memory is a dataset, not a bolt-on cache. Future agents should be able to query it as first-class RDF." .
spec:comment-24a59a77 a ekga:Comment ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "The spec leans on Ontop for RDBMS virtualization because it gives a SPARQL entry point without ETL and preserves PK/FK semantics as properties." .
spec:comment-89eafb0b a ekga:Comment ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Holonic ingest assumes the `holonic` library's four-graph holon model as the canonical shape for imported holons." .
spec:openissue-fb76ed8b a ekga:OpenIssue ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Domain ontology scope is undefined. Recommendation: ship a stub `ekga-core` ontology and require each deployment to declare a `ekga:DomainExtension` that imports it." .
spec:openissue-05182045 a ekga:OpenIssue ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Entity resolution thresholds and human-in-the-loop policy are unspecified. Recommendation: define a `ekga:ResolutionPolicy` shape with fields for similarity metric, threshold, and review requirement." .
spec:openissue-0cafba0a a ekga:OpenIssue ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "SHACL-to-form rendering lacks a chosen library. Recommendation: evaluate `shacl-form` (web component) and `rdf-form`; pick one before UI work begins." .
spec:openissue-78b8bd3a a ekga:OpenIssue ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "LLM extraction promotion policy (auto vs reviewed) is not defined. Recommendation: default to reviewed for v1." .
spec:openissue-1ecc92f2 a ekga:OpenIssue ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "GCC High specifics (certificate pinning, FIPS mode, audit retention) need a dedicated compliance annex." .
spec:openissue-712e996e a ekga:OpenIssue ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Versioning strategy for the KG itself (named-graph snapshots vs quad-level diffs) is undecided. Recommendation: start with named-graph snapshots plus PROV-O activity log." .
spec:openissue-a16d9a26 a ekga:OpenIssue ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Vector store governance: are embeddings a first-class RDF resource or opaque? Recommendation: first-class, with `ekga:Embedding` class and IRI back-link." .
spec:openissue-b51a1250 a ekga:OpenIssue ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Backup and restore semantics across the three stores must be transactional or explicitly eventually consistent. Recommendation: document as eventually consistent with reconciliation job." .
spec:openissue-f83696bd a ekga:OpenIssue ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Rate limiting and quotas for LLM connectors are unspecified." .
spec:openissue-a55a644a a ekga:OpenIssue ; ekga:partOf spec:ekga-001 ; dct:description "Chat memory retention, redaction, and user export rights are unspecified." .
